description.narrative: RO technical assistance, capacity development and knowledge leadership contribute to the improvement of Infant and Young Child Feeding Practices, and Maternal Nutrition programming in 12 high burden ESA countriesincluding capacity for CCC delivery., which contributes to Child Health, Operations Support To Programme Delivery, Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition, Technical Excellence In Policy And Programmes, Treatment Of Severe Acute Malnutrition. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: ESA country programmes and humanitarian action (reflect global and regional priorities and strategies), are based on solid evidence, employ good practices and conform to highest technical standards.
